S'{{Infobox congressman\n|birthname     =\n|name          = Steve Knight\n|image         = Steve Knight.jpg\n|state         = [[California]]\n|district      = [[California\'s 25th congressional district|25th]]\n|term_start    = January 3, 2015\n|term_end      = \n|succeeding    = [[Buck McKeon]]\n|succeeded     = \n|state_senate2   = California State\n|district2       = [[California\'s 21st Senate district|21st]]\n|term_start2     = December 3, 2012\n|term_end2       = \n|predecessor2    = [[Sharon Runner]] \'\'(redistricted)\'\'\n|successor2      = \n|state_assembly3 = California\n|district3      = [[California\'s 36th State Assembly district|36th]]\n|term_start3    = December 1, 2008\n|term_end3      = November 30, 2012\n|predecessor3   = [[Sharon Runner]]\n|successor3     = [[Steve Fox (politician)|Steve Fox]]\n|office4        = [[Palmdale, California|Palmdale]] City Councillor\n|term_start4     = December 5, 2005\n|term_end4       = December 1, 2008\n|predecessor4    = \n|successor4      = [[Laura Bettencourt]]\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1966|12|17}}\n|birth_place    = [[Edwards Air Force Base]], [[California]]\n|death_date     = \n|death_place    = \n|nationality    = [[United States|American]]\n|party          = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|spouse         = Lily Knight\n|residence      = [[Palmdale, California|Palmdale]], [[California]]\n|occupation     = Politician\n|profession     = Police officer\n|religion       = \n|signature      = \n|website        = \n|footnotes      = \n<!--Military service-->\n|allegiance     = [[United States]]\n|branch         = [[United States Army|Army]]\n}}\n\n\'\'\'Stephen Knight\'\'\' (born December 17, 1966<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/Steve-Knight-for-Senate/283938464089?sk=info|title=Steve Knight Facebook page}}</ref>) is an [[United States|American]] politician. He represents the [[California\'s 21st Senate district|21st]] district in the [[California State Senate]], encompassing northeastern [[Los Angeles County, California|Los Angeles]] and western [[San Bernardino County, California|San Bernardino]] counties in the [[High Desert (California)|High Desert]] region. He is also congressman-elect for California\'s 25th Congressional District.  He supported Proposition 8<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.montereyherald.com/ci_11729329|title=Panel backs Prop. 8 challenge|work=montereyherald.com}}</ref> that was ruled unconstitutional by SCOTUS on June 26, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/supreme-court-rules-gay-marriage-cases/story?id=19492896|title=The Supreme Court Rules on DOMA and Proposition 8 Cases - ABC News|work=ABC News}}</ref> Knight opposed bi-lingual education in a mostly latino populated city<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palmdale,_California#Demographics|title=Palmdale, California|publisher=}}</ref> and courted further controversy in voting against the images of the Confederate flag being removed from state property.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/political/la-me-pc-steve-knight-flag-20140827-story.html|title=Confederate flag vote puts Knight on spot in congressional race|date=27 August 2014|work=latimes.com}}</ref> Knight has consistently voted against an increase of minimum wage, gun control with semi-automatic weapons and water regulations for the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://votesmart.org/candidate/key-votes/71098/steve-knight#.VDc2W_fn_mQ|title=Project Vote Smart - The Voter\'s Self Defense System|work=Project Vote Smart}}</ref>\nHe currently lives in [[Palmdale, California|Palmdale]] with his wife Lily and two children.\n\nHe also served in the California State Assembly from 2008-2012.\n\nHis father, [[William J. Knight|William J. "Pete" Knight]], represented geographically similar Senate and Assembly districts from 1992 to 2004.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://cssrc.us/web/21/}}\n* [http://steveknight.org/ Campaign website]\n\n{{California State Senate}}\n\n{{Persondata <!-- Metadata: see [[Wikipedia:Persondata]]. -->\n| NAME              = Knight, Steve\n| ALTERNATIVE NAMES =\n| SHORT DESCRIPTION = American politician\n| DATE OF BIRTH     = December 17, 1966\n| PLACE OF BIRTH    = [[Edwards Air Force Base]], [[California]]\n| DATE OF DEATH     =\n| PLACE OF DEATH    =\n}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Knight, Steve}}\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:California city council members]]\n[[Category:California Republicans]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles Police Department officers]]\n[[Category:California State Senators]]\n[[Category:Members of the California State Assembly]]\n[[Category:People from Kern County, California]]\n[[Category:People from Palmdale, California]]\n[[Category:United States Army officers]]'
